    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of alder native to Europe, the British Isles, and Africa, and cultivated in the United States.  Known as black alder for its dark bark and cones.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
